---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MainHeader from '../components/common/MainHeader.astro';
---

<Layout
    title='Privacy Policy - KASANE - 襲'
    description='Read our privacy policy to understand how we handle your data.'
>
    <div class='flex flex-col min-h-screen'>
        <main class='max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 md:py-20'>
            <MainHeader
                mainTitle='Privacy Policy'
                subTitle='Protection of Your Data'
            />

            <div class='space-y-16 max-w-3xl mx-auto text-stone-700'>
                <div
                    class='prose prose-stone leading-loose text-stone-600 space-y-6'
                >
                    <p>
                        At KASANE, we believe that your creative data belongs to
                        you. As a client-side focused toolkit, our philosophy is
                        simple:
                        <strong
                            >we do not collect, store, or share your personal
                            information.</strong
                        >
                    </p>
                </div>

                <section class='space-y-6'>
                    <h2
                        class='text-xl font-bold text-stone-800 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-3'
                    >
                        <span class='w-8 h-px bg-stone-300'></span>
                        1. Data Collection & Local Storage
                    </h2>
                    <div
                        class='bg-stone-50 border border-stone-100 rounded-2xl p-8 space-y-4'
                    >
                        <p class='text-stone-600 leading-relaxed'>
                            This website operates primarily in your browser. Any
                            preferences you save—such as your
                            <strong
                                >brand colors, palette history, or theme
                                settings</strong
                            >—are stored locally on your device using
                            <code
                                class='text-xs bg-stone-200 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded'
                                >localStorage</code
                            >.
                        </p>
                        <p class='text-stone-600 leading-relaxed'>
                            This data never leaves your device and is never
                            transmitted to our servers. You have full control
                            over this data and can clear it at any time by
                            clearing your browser's cache.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </section>

                <section class='space-y-6'>
                    <h2
                        class='text-xl font-bold text-stone-800 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-3'
                    >
                        <span class='w-8 h-px bg-stone-300'></span>
                        2. Third-Party Services
                    </h2>
                    <p class='text-stone-600 leading-relaxed'>
                        We use minimal third-party services to ensure the
                        website functions correctly. However, we do not use
                        tracking pixels or advertising cookies that follow you
                        across the web.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class='space-y-6'>
                    <h2
                        class='text-xl font-bold text-stone-800 tracking-tight flex items-center gap-3'
                    >
                        <span class='w-8 h-px bg-stone-300'></span>
                        3. Changes to This Policy
                    </h2>
                    <p class='text-stone-600 leading-relaxed'>
                        We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time.
                        Thus, we advise you to review this page periodically for
                        any changes. These changes are effective immediately
                        after they are posted on this page.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class='border-t border-stone-200 pt-10'>
                    <p class='text-sm text-stone-400 text-center'>
                        Last updated: {
                            new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', {
                                year: 'numeric',
                                month: 'long',
                                day: 'numeric',
                            })
                        }
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </main>
    </div>
</Layout>
